      "title": "Apply for visa soon; UK tells students",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The British High Commission in Sri Lanka has called on students to apply for their visa to the United Kingdom as early as possible as the decision to process would take five weeks.",
        "\u201cWe receive higher number of applications in August so you should start preparing your application and submit now,\u201d the High Commission tweeted.",
        "-Depending on your personal circumstances and where you are applying from, you may also need:",
        "Proof that you can pay for your course fees and maintenance for one academic year. The amount on your personal circumstances.",
        "-If you are waiting for your CAS reference number, you can prepare your supporting documents, and in the meantime."
      ],
